The paper discusses a communication strategy for multiple access channels, which involves splitting information streams and adapting transmissions to channel states. This topic falls under the field of information theory (cs.IT) and networked systems (cs.NI). The paper also discusses the trade-off among different rates, which is a common theme in communication engineering (cs.CE) and multimedia systems (cs.MM). Additionally, the paper proposes a decoding strategy for the receiver, which falls under the category of signal processing (cs.SI).
